title: Open Spaces (publicly accessible, includes parks)
name: Open Spaces (publicly accessible, includes parks)
description:
Geodatabase description:
 
'OpenSpace.mdb' was created in May 2008.  It is an accumlation of data from varous people, agencies and methods.  This information is included in the attributes.  There are three features in this geodatabase.  One is all of California included for extent purposes, the other two contain the same data, one is a point feature, the other is a polygon feature.
 
Attributes for the open space features include:
 
SOURCE: Name of original shapefile or geodatabase feature that the data is derived from.

COLLECTED: Person who collected the data.

NAME: Name of open space.

OWNER: Owner of open space.

ADDRESS: Address of open space.

MAPBLKLOT: Parel number of open space, this was derived by spatial join of the point feature.  If the point fell on a parcel, that parcel is used for this attribute.

The projection of this feature is NAD 1983 StatePlane California III FIPS 0403 (Feet).
 
This abstract is the extent of any user entered metadata for this geodatabase, for any questions regarding this feature please contact Michael Webster, GIS Analyst, City and County of San Francisco, Planning Department at michael.webster@sfgov.org or 415-575-9067.
